://auto.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/passenger-vehicle/cars/hyundai-motors-launches-service-campaigns/62280339|title=Hyundai Motors launches service campaigns \u2013 ET Auto|website=ETAuto.com}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|title=Hyundai launches anniversary edition of Santro priced up to Rs 5.75 lakh |url=https://connectgujarat.com/hyundai-launches-anniversary-edition-of-santro-priced-up-to-rs-5-75-lakh/|publisher=Connect Gujarat|accessdate=23 Oct 2019}}</ref> HMIL also operates its own dealerships known as Hyundai Motor Plazas in large metros across India. HMIL has the second largest sales and service network in India after [[Maruti Suzuki]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/hyundai-s-price-jolt-for-maruti-114031201116_1.html|title=Hyundai's price jolt for Maruti|first=Sharmistha|last=Mukherjee|date=12 March 2014|publisher=|via=Business Standard}}</ref>\n\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:97%; text-align:right;\"\n|+Hyundai Motor India Limited annual sales\n|-\n!Year||Domestic sales||Exports||Total\n|-\n|1998||8,447||0||8,447\n|-\n|1999||17,627||20||17,647\n|-\n|2000||82,896||3,823||86,719\n|-\n|2001||87,175||6,092||93,267\n|-\n|2002||102,806||8,245||111,051\n|-\n|2003||120,325||30,416||150,741\n|-\n|2004||139,759||75,871||215,630\n|-\n|2005||156,291||96,560||252,851\n|-\n|2006||186,174||113,339||299,513\n|-\n|2007||200,411||126,749||327,160\n|-\n|2008||245,397||243,919||489,316\n|-\n|2009||289,863||270,017||559,880\n|-\n|2010||356,717||247,102||603,819\n|-\n|2011||373,709||242,330||616,039\n|-\n|2012||391,276||250,005||641,281\n|-\n|2013||380,000||233,260||613,260\n|-\n|2014||410,000||191,221||601,221\n|-\n|2015||476,001||167,268||643,269\n|-\n|2016||500,537||161,517||662,054\n|-\n|2017||527,320||150,901||678,221\n|-\n|2018||550,002||160,010||710,012\n|-\n|2019||510,260||181,200||691,460<br />\n|}\n</center>\n\n==Exports==\nHMIL currently exports vehicles to over 92 countries across [[Africa]], [[Middle East]], [[Latin America]], [[Australia]] and [[Asia]]. It has been India's number one exporter for the last 10 years consecutively.{{when|date=April 2020}}\n\nIn February 2010 HMIL achieved a record export of 1 million units.\n\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hyundai.com/in/en/AboutUs/HyundaiMotorIndia/WhoWeAre/index.html|title=Who We Are \u2013 HYUNDAI MOTOR INDIA \u2013 NEW THINKING. NEW POSSIBILITIES.|website=www.hyundai.com}}</ref> HMIL has been consecutively awarded \"Top Exporter Of The Year\" for 10 years by EEPC.The Highest Exported volume was 2,70,017 in year 2009. Now, it has moved down as fourth largest car exporter following Maruti Suzuki, [[Volkswagen India|Volkswagen]] and Nissan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/maruti-is-top-passenger-car-exporter-from-india/article19901821.ece|title=Maruti is top passenger car exporter from India|date=22 October 2017|publisher=|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref>\n\n==Sales performance==\nHyundai Motor India Ltd is the country's second largest car manufacturer and the largest passenger car exporter, and cumulative sales stood at 6,78,221 units in 2017.\n\nHyundai's Grand-i10, Elite-i20 and Creta have cumulatively achieved 1.3 million sales in less than four years which includes 1.1 million domestic and 0.29 million for exports.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n*Sales trend\n----\n**1998 8,447 units \n----\n**2000 85,640 (exports 3,824)\n----\n**2005 252,851 (exports 96,560)\n----\n**2010 603,820 (exports 247,102)\n----\n**2015 643,270 (exports 167,269)\n\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Hyundai Exports up by 4.6%- BigGaddi.com News |url=http://www.biggaddi.com/News_Detail.asp?News_Event_ID=11262 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130806111829/http://www.biggaddi.com/News_Detail.asp?News_Event_ID=11262 |url-status=dead |archive-date=6 August 2013 |publisher=BigGaddi.com |accessdate=8 June 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Awards and achievements==\n*'''Indian Car of the Year (ICOTY)'''\n**2008 \u2014 Hyundai i10\n**2014 \u2014 Hyundai Grand i10\n**2015 \u2014 Hyundai Elite i20\n**2016 \u2014 Hyundai Creta\n**2018 \u2014 Hyundai Verna \n**2020 \u2014 Hyundai Venue\n*J D Power Appeal Awards 2016 demonstrating excellence of 'Made In India' Products as per global standards for Grand i10, Elite i20 & Creta.\n*JD Power Indian Customer Satisfaction Award 2017 \u2013 For Ranking Number 1 in After Sales Customer satisfaction.\n\n==Brand ambassador==\nThe carmaker got [[Shah Rukh Khan]] on board as its brand ambassador for the Hyundai Xcent, the company's recently launched sub-compact sedan in India. I998, SRK shot his first TVC for the Hyundai Santro, and his association with the car brand has now turned 19.\n\nIn 2010 Khan won the \"Brand Ambassador of the Year\" for Hyundai i10 at NDTV Profit Car and Bike Awards.\n\nKhan also promotes the \"Be The Better Guy\" road safety campaign for Hyundai.\n\nIn July 2017, Hyundai India extended Khan's contract for two years.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shah Rukh Khan as brand ambassador for Hyundai Xcent in India |url=http://carandme.com/media/news/shah-rukh-khan-to-be-new-brand-ambassador-for-hyundai/ |publisher=CarAndMe.com |accessdate=23 September 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150622132422/http://carandme.com/media/news/shah-rukh-khan-to-be-new-brand-ambassador-for-hyundai/ |archivedate=22 June 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Shah Rukh Khan as brand ambassador for Hyundai Xcent in India | url=http://www.zigwheels.com/news-features/news/shah-rukh-khan-roped-in-as-brand-ambassador-for-hyundai-xcent/19766/|publisher=ZigWheels.com|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Hyundai Motor Company]]\n* [[Hyundai Kia Automotive Group]]\n* [[Automobile industry in India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hyundai.co.in Hyundai Motor India Limited]\n*[http://www.techrasta.com/2015/05/hyundai-india.html Hyundai history]\n\n{{Hyundai Motor Company}}\n{{Korean automobile indu